<module>
  <h>agus</h>
  <p><g>agus</g>
    <en>and</en> is a conjunction.</p>

  <section>
    <h>dependents</h>
    <section id="deps-verbs">
      <h>independent verb forms</h>
      <p><g>agus</g> can conjoin independent verb forms – <xl>
          <li>
            <gd><m>Tha</m> an cù aig an dorus agus <m>tha</m> an cat aig an teine.</gd>
            <tr>The dog is at the door and the cat is by the fire.</tr>
            <ref text="617">td. 6</ref>
          </li>
          <li>
            <gd><m>Tha</m> an dorus mór agus <m>tha</m> an teine mór.</gd>
            <tr>The door is big and the fire is big.</tr>
            <ref text="617">td. 6</ref>
          </li>
        </xl>
      </p>
    </section>
    <section id="deps-proper">
      <h>proper nouns</h>
      <p><g>agus</g> can conjoin proper nouns – <xl>
          <li>
            <gd>Tha <m>Màiri agus Calum</m> ag obair anns an achadh an diugh.</gd>
            <tr>Mary and Malcolm are working in the field today.</tr>
            <ref text="617">td. 6–7</ref>
          </li>
        </xl></p>
    </section>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h>uses</h>
    <section id="uses-root">
      <h>root</h>
      <p>When conjoining independent verb forms, <g>agus</g> constitutes the root of a sentence – <xl>
          <li>
            <gd>Tha an cù aig an dorus <m>agus</m> tha an cat aig an teine.</gd>
            <tr>The dog is at the door and the cat is by the fire.</tr>
            <ref text="617">td. 6</ref>
          </li>
          <li>
            <gd>Tha sibh trang ag obair anns an achadh <m>agus</m> tha sibh sgìth.</gd>
            <tr>You are busy working in the field and you are tired.</tr>
            <ref text="617">td. 7</ref>
          </li>
        </xl></p>
    </section>
    <section id="uses-sbj">
      <h>subject</h>
      <p>When conjoining two nouns, <g>agus</g> can function as the subject of a verb – <xl>
          <li>
            <gd>Tha <m>Màiri agus Calum</m> trang an diugh – tha iad ag obair anns an achadh.</gd>
            <tr>Mary and Malcolm are busy today – they are working in the field.</tr>
            <ref text="617">td. 7</ref>
          </li>
        </xl></p>
    </section>
  </section>

